Package edu.csupomona.cs.cs141.prog_assgnmntFINAL

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    BallOfEnergy
    Of course every entity is simply a cute little ball of energy.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AmmoIncrease
    AmmoIncrease is a subclass of PowerUp, and its purpose is to add an additional bullet to the player's ammunition cartridge.
    Enemy
    Enemy is the threat of the game.
    Engine
    The Engine is what runs the actual statistics and calculations of the game.
    Invincibility
    A subclass of PowerUp, this class is used to set the player to an invincible state.
    PowerUp
    Power up class is set up to give the player the advantage of the game.
    Radar
    Radar is a subclass of PowerUp, and its main intention is to reveal the document that hides behind one of the rooms in the world.
    Room
    Room is the class that holds the document.
    Runner
    The main class of the game.
    SaveLoad
    This class is intended to save a progress of the game that the player currently is in, and to load the saved game upon starting up the program again.
    Spy
    The spy class, or otherwise known as the player class, is the main protagonist of the game world, the hero that is to be controlled by the one who is going to play.
    UserInterface
    User interface is inteded to display and run the game in a text format for the user.
